<blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-lang="en"><p lang="en" dir="ltr">Domain driven design talk at <a href="https://twitter.com/hashtag/EuroIA17?src=hash&amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">#EuroIA17</a> <a href="https://t.co/eII4dGKoj8">pic.twitter.com/eII4dGKoj8</a></p>&mdash; Mark Foley (@folomarco) <a href="https://twitter.com/folomarco/status/913390773344915456?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">September 28, 2017</a></blockquote>
</div>

Reviewing work to rein in some 50 different domains, Anya Somerville, Silver Oliver and Michael Smethurst presented on [Domain Driven Design at UK Parliament](https://euroia.org/sessions/domain-driven-design-at-uk-parliament).

To discover what is closest to the truth, they noted the importance of talk therapy to get stakeholders relaxed and open. Often this revealed the important things which no one had previously thought to mention.

Also of importance was to keep the [rather complex concept domain driven design](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Domain-driven_design) as an inclusive and facilitating process — avoiding past incidents where those who could not master IA-speak were simply forced out.
